comment: Initial grammar example generation was assisted by WBUR's AUML combinatorial generator. Note that I'm hoping the systems are able to fairly reliably distinguish later from latest; if not, one or the other may need to drop out. TODO REVIEW: Synonyms can be implemented as custom input types, reducing the combinatoric explosion of alternative phrasings... but I'm not sure how that interacts with system-level attempts to guess generalizations from the examples. Hold off for now. TODO FUTURE: It's been suggested that an AUML-like plug-in for Jovo could be useful.
